		// 			<div className='body'>
		// 				<p>
		// 					I studied physics at Universidade Federal do Paraná (Curitiba, Brazil), where I developed a 
		// 					strong foundation in theoretical and computational methods. Later, I earned my M.Sc. and Ph.D. 
		// 					degrees from Universidade Federal do Rio Grande do Sul (Porto Alegre, Brazil), with a collaborative
		// 					research period at the Statistical Mechanics and Condensed Matter Group of the Institute of Physical 
		// 					Chemistry Rocasolano (Madrid, Spain). My doctoral and postdoctoral work focused on statistical mechanics, 
		// 					phase transitions, and complex systems, particularly in lattice gas models and associating fluids.

		// 					From 2017 to 2021, I worked as a postdoctoral researcher at the Physics Department of Universidade Federal 
		// 					de Minas Gerais (Belo Horizonte, Brazil), collaborating with Prof. Ronald Dickman. My research explored:
		// 					 - Jamming and percolation phenomena in restricted-valence systems (Phys. Rev. Research).
		// 					 - Phase transitions in associating lattice gases, revealing critical behaviors analogous to liquid-liquid equilibria (Phys. Rev. E).
		// 					 - Water-like anomalies in confined systems and mixtures, providing insights into thermodynamic and structural 
		// 					 properties (J. Chem. Phys.).
		// 					 - Ecological modeling, where I applied statistical physics to study habitat fragmentation and species survival (Physica A).
		// 				</p>

		// 				<p>
		// 					Building on my physics research background, I've transitioned into data engineering, 
		// 					progressing from data analysis to technical leadership. My career began developing Power 
		// 					BI dashboards and implementing business rules as a Data Analyst. This evolved into building 
		// 					robust data infrastructure as a Data Engineer, where I configured AWS services (EMR, EKS), 
		// 					automated deployments with Terraform, and orchestrated Spark jobs via Airflow. As a Platform Engineer 
		// 					at Z-Tech/BEES, I designed and managed cloud infrastructure on Azure, developing CI/CD pipelines with 
		// 					Kubernetes and creating data observability systems using Airflow and PySpark. Currently, as Tech Lead 
		// 					at BEES, I lead data platform initiatives including a secure Databricks Delta-sharing solution for 
		// 					partner collaboration and an innovative automation framework integrating Jira with Terraform for 
		// 					infrastructure management. Beyond technical projects, I mentor team members and contribute to technical 
		// 					hiring, fostering team growth while maintaining hands-on involvement in system architecture and 
		// 					implementation.

		// 					My work consistently focuses on creating scalable, automated solutions that bridge business needs with 
		// 					technical execution, applying the same analytical rigor from my academic research to solve complex 
		// 					data challenges.
		// 				</p>
		// 			</div>
